00:23.490 --> 00:27.097
DAYS TO CHRISTMAS

00:36.937 --> 00:38.575
[ Engine Revs Outside ]

00:43.010 --> 00:46.287
This is what's been worrying me-

00:47.281 --> 00:51.787
Drilling sample number 76,
from 1300 foot.

00:51.885 --> 00:55.196
See. we've finally found something
else than just plain rocks and dirt.

00:56.957 --> 00:59.301
Have a look for yourself, sir-

01:10.437 --> 01:12.917
Sawdust. Mmm.

01:12.973 --> 01:17.285
See. at first. I thought we'd drilled
into some old tree or something.

01:18.111 --> 01:20.057
BUT HO,

01:20.113 --> 01:25.654
This level of sawdust
is 65 foot thick.

01:26.453 --> 01:29.161
I mean, it doesn't add up,
It doesn't make sense.

01:29.823 --> 01:30.824
It does,

01:33.760 --> 01:37.264
In the olden days.
people used to store ice...

01:37.331 --> 01:40.608
by encasing it in sawdust-

01:41.902 --> 01:44.644
Yeah. but what do you mean?
What are you trying to say?

01:44.738 --> 01:48.185
This mountain
is like a giant icebox

01:48.275 --> 01:50.186
For storing what?

01:51.178 --> 01:54.455
Drill deeper...
and you will see.

01:54.514 --> 01:58.860
[Creaking In Distance] Well, I am.
They're drilling as we speak.

02:01.355 --> 02:04.700
[ Men Shouting]

02:07.594 --> 02:10.871
Make sure everyone has one of these.
What are these?

02:11.999 --> 02:13.842
It's the new
safety instructions.

02:13.934 --> 02:18.144
Wash behind the ears.
[ Chuckles] This is funny shit. si-

02:18.205 --> 02:20.151
Watch your mouth!

02:20.207 --> 02:26.021
It's Christmas time.
so let's act like it.

02:27.814 --> 02:32.695
[Engine Revs]

02:33.220 --> 02:35.496
[Speaking Finnish ]
Some-one's coming. Shh.

02:35.555 --> 02:38.126
[ Man Speaking English ] Mr. Greene.
I think we've found something.

02:38.191 --> 02:43.334
[Engine Puttering]

02:46.233 --> 02:50.875
Sample number 98.
I think you were right.

03:07.354 --> 03:09.925
Always believe,

03:11.892 --> 03:14.429
Always,

03:31.011 --> 03:34.515
Gentlemen, listen up,

03:35.415 --> 03:39.420
My dream since my early childhood."

03:39.953 --> 03:42.433
is about to come true,

03:52.699 --> 03:56.044
I can proudly say."

03:56.937 --> 04:01.079
that we are standing
on a sacred grave.

04:01.141 --> 04:06.716
On the biggest burial mound
in the world.

04:06.780 --> 04:08.259
[ In Finnish ]
Someone's buried here.

04:08.315 --> 04:13.663
[Continues In English ] This remarkable
place puts even the pyramids to shame.

04:14.488 --> 04:17.992
It took the Sami people of Lapland...,,

04:18.091 --> 04:21.334
centuries to build this mountain,

04:22.295 --> 04:26.766
You have 24 days to open it,

04:26.833 --> 04:28.608
Roll up your sleeves-

04:28.668 --> 04:31.308
Prepare the dynamite.

04:31.404 --> 04:34.010
Do what you do best.
[ In Finnish ] They're going to blow it up.

04:36.009 --> 04:39.513
You have a grave to rob,

04:42.682 --> 04:44.025
[In Finnish]
Juuso!

04:46.753 --> 04:50.667
Juuso, wait!

04:51.324 --> 04:53.031
BORDER ZONE- NO ACCESS

04:54.861 --> 04:57.137
[ In Finnish ]
I think Santa is buried up there.

04:58.431 --> 05:00.877
[Panting]

05:03.670 --> 05:06.844
[Panting]

05:08.608 --> 05:12.818
Juuso, is Santa Claus dead?

05:12.879 --> 05:16.884
What a baby.
You still believe in Santa?

05:17.384 --> 05:18.727
Come om,

05:20.520 --> 05:23.899
They've been lying to us.
To you.

05:24.558 --> 05:26.868
Who was the Santa
who came to our house then?

05:26.960 --> 05:29.566
Mr. Piiparinen.
Haven't you figured that out yet?

05:30.330 --> 05:33.209
Do you think Dad knows?

05:33.700 --> 05:35.907
Your dad pays him for it,

05:36.403 --> 05:41.375
Don't you get it?
This whole Christmas thing is just a bluff.

05:41.474 --> 05:44.387
[Explosion]

06:14.875 --> 06:16.718
<i>THE TRUTH ABOUT SANTA CLAUS <i></i></i>

06:19.279 --> 06:22.123
<i>THE FIRST SANTA CLAUS <i></i></i>

06:29.789 --> 06:30.893
<i>WHO'S BEEN NAUGHTY? <i></i></i>

06:44.137 --> 06:45.912
<i>Santa walking barefoot in the snow.<i></i></i>

07:14.167 --> 07:15.976
<i>Ancient Santa by his cauldron <i></i></i>

07:48.201 --> 07:51.774
DAY TO CHRISTMAS

08:15.295 --> 08:18.742
[Grunting]

08:28.575 --> 08:30.350
[Sighs]

08:57.370 --> 09:02.115
[Wolves Howling]

09:21.961 --> 09:22.962
Pietari!

09:24.764 --> 09:27.404
[In Finnish]
Wake up,Son!

09:39.379 --> 09:42.087
[Bang]
[Yelps]

09:42.148 --> 09:45.595
[Groans]

09:45.652 --> 09:49.065
[Father In Finnish]
Pietari! Are you awake?

09:51.391 --> 09:55.339
[In Finnish] Yeah. yeah!
Them go and get cleaned up'

10:00.433 --> 10:02.435
[Bell Jingles]

10:02.502 --> 10:06.006
Vuppe, bad boy.
You were supposed to keep watch.

10:34.033 --> 10:36.013
[Gasps]

10:36.102 --> 10:38.548
[Door Creaks]

10:49.215 --> 10:51.161
[Banging]

10:51.217 --> 10:52.890
Dad!

10:53.887 --> 10:56.697
Come here, Dad!

10:56.789 --> 10:59.668
Come inside
if you have something to say

11:00.493 --> 11:02.404
I don't want to,

11:02.495 --> 11:05.738
You shouldn't
be out there alone,

11:05.832 --> 11:09.405
Really, I've got something
important to tell you.

11:10.069 --> 11:14.415
Really, the wolves
will gobble you up.

11:14.507 --> 11:16.509
And I'm not kidding,

11:24.551 --> 11:26.758
Dad, I'm coming in now-

11:27.754 --> 11:31.861
Close your eyes. Son.
Daddy's working.

11:37.096 --> 11:40.373
[Thudding]

11:40.433 --> 11:43.107
You shouldn't have
turned the lights off.

11:43.203 --> 11:45.615
Who'd ever look at them
at night?

11:46.439 --> 11:49.283
- Have you been on the roof?
- What?

11:49.876 --> 11:52.447
Outside my window?

11:53.279 --> 11:59.286
I'm too busy to
answer stupid questions.

12:01.287 --> 12:05.064
- Have you or haven't you?
- No. I haven't.

12:05.124 --> 12:06.626
Maybe the chimney sweep-

12:06.726 --> 12:10.264
Go and get dressed!
We're leaving soon.

12:10.363 --> 12:12.070
Where to?

12:12.699 --> 12:14.872
Don't you remember what day it is?

12:14.934 --> 12:17.244
Yeah, the round-up.
You're taking me along?

12:17.303 --> 12:20.443
I thought you'd
be dressed by now

12:38.424 --> 12:40.665
He's spying on us,

13:22.001 --> 13:23.674
This is yours now,

13:24.804 --> 13:26.374
Is it loaded?

13:26.472 --> 13:31.683
Of course. or it'd be useless.
And take those goggles off.

13:34.480 --> 13:36.824
Have you got a light?

13:38.484 --> 13:40.327
Where! your dad?

13:40.386 --> 13:42.332
They had to take
the snowmobiles,

13:42.388 --> 13:44.163
Piiparinen couldn't
get the chopper started.

13:44.223 --> 13:48.569
Keep away from the fence!
Three, two, one!

13:50.830 --> 13:54.004
[Men Shouting]
Whoa!

13:58.971 --> 14:02.919
You really think you can use that?
Of course I can.

14:03.843 --> 14:08.019
You gonna shoot Santa Claus?
He was outside my window last night.

14:09.349 --> 14:12.592
I thought you said he was dead.

14:12.685 --> 14:15.689
Electric fence.
How do you like it?

14:16.522 --> 14:18.195
Protection.

14:18.257 --> 14:22.865
The explosions in the mountain
have sent the wolves on the prowl.

14:22.929 --> 14:24.738
[ Father] Wonder what
they're digging up there?

14:25.865 --> 14:27.936
Just samples, I guess.

14:28.034 --> 14:29.604
Look!

14:34.941 --> 14:38.047
[ Chuckles]
They're coming!

14:38.111 --> 14:40.216
[Cheering]

14:40.279 --> 14:42.850
[ Pietari]
Dad, Dad!

14:42.915 --> 14:44.588
They're coming!

14:46.953 --> 14:50.298
Our freezers will soon
be brimming with meat.

14:52.792 --> 14:53.930
Open the gate.

14:54.026 --> 14:55.130
Out of the way!

14:58.131 --> 14:59.769
Come on!

14:59.866 --> 15:04.144
Get in here, now!
What's keeping you?

15:12.478 --> 15:14.321
[ Blonde Man ]
Two skinny runts.

15:15.148 --> 15:16.320
Something's wrong.

15:17.617 --> 15:19.790
Maybe the others got lost.

15:27.326 --> 15:29.306
No, they didn't.

16:01.828 --> 16:05.207
[Engines Stop]

16:15.007 --> 16:16.509
Merry Christmas.

16:22.949 --> 16:24.451
You stay here.

16:24.517 --> 16:27.623
Me, too?
Keep an eye on Pietari.

17:01.354 --> 17:04.198
What kind of wolves
would do this?

17:04.257 --> 17:08.204
Big and nasty ones.
Come and take a look.

17:09.729 --> 17:12.539
Those morons
and their blasting!

17:14.200 --> 17:16.612
Now we have to deal with
Russian wolves as well!

17:17.904 --> 17:19.781
They found the hole.

17:20.339 --> 17:23.718
This was cut with pliers.

17:25.944 --> 17:28.221
This is our fault.

17:28.281 --> 17:32.388
If you go crying to your dad,
I'll give you a flogging.

17:32.451 --> 17:35.261
We were never
anywhere near the gate.

17:40.626 --> 17:43.266
We should shoot that lot of idiots.

17:43.362 --> 17:47.435
[ Blonde Man ] They've probably gone by now.
It's been quiet for days.

17:48.734 --> 17:53.479
[Dark Haired Man] If it wasn't for that
border, I'd make minced meat of them.

17:57.310 --> 18:02.157
[Blonde Man] We have insurance, right?
No, we bloody well don't.

18:08.254 --> 18:10.791
433 carcasses.

18:10.890 --> 18:13.769
Aimo,
how much is that worth?

18:16.329 --> 18:18.331
Around $85,000.

18:20.833 --> 18:23.677
Plus 22% VAT.

18:31.811 --> 18:35.020
All that money's
been rotted away.

18:42.188 --> 18:44.759
[Sniffs]

18:44.824 --> 18:47.202
He sure was hungry.

18:48.361 --> 18:50.034
What do we do?

18:52.198 --> 18:54.371
We'll pay them a little visit.

18:56.702 --> 18:58.545
Nuts!

18:59.271 --> 19:04.653
The guards have been paid
to shoot anyone who comes near.

19:04.710 --> 19:06.690
Crossing the border
is not a small thing.

19:06.779 --> 19:09.316
Neither is bankruptcy.

19:09.382 --> 19:11.555
Pietari, come on!

19:44.984 --> 19:48.090
[Engine Stops]
This was one hell of an idea!

20:01.100 --> 20:05.571
[Radio Chatter]

20:05.671 --> 20:07.742
[Chatter; Static ]

20:11.544 --> 20:15.515
[Chatter Static Continue ]

20:25.591 --> 20:27.468
These boys left in a hurry.

20:28.360 --> 20:29.930
[Grunts, Mutters]
[Objects Clatter]

20:31.597 --> 20:34.305
[Wind Howls]

20:39.138 --> 20:42.142
[Bang Echoes]

20:45.811 --> 20:47.813
[Yells]
Come and see!

20:47.913 --> 20:52.157
[Radio Chatter Continues ]

21:12.338 --> 21:15.148
They found him, Vuppe.

21:18.144 --> 21:21.990
Seismic researchers, my ass!
They've excavated something.

21:27.186 --> 21:28.961
What on earth
did they dig up?

21:43.702 --> 21:48.048
[Wind Howls]
[Metal Creaking]

21:49.608 --> 21:51.884
So much for that.

21:53.546 --> 21:55.651
[Metal Creaking]

22:09.495 --> 22:11.566
[Bird Hooting]

22:27.179 --> 22:30.820
What are you doing?
Aren't you going to open it?

22:31.650 --> 22:33.061
NO.

22:38.424 --> 22:40.404
Tape these on your bum.

22:41.227 --> 22:42.934
Are you serious?

22:47.867 --> 22:49.574
How do I look?

22:49.668 --> 22:52.012
Like a kid in a diaper.

22:52.071 --> 22:54.608
You brought me here
just for this?

22:57.376 --> 22:58.582
Look.

23:09.288 --> 23:13.532
The real Santa was totally different.
The Coca-Cola Santa is just a hoax.

23:15.628 --> 23:17.107
These are from some fairy tale.

23:18.197 --> 23:19.437
This isn't.

23:22.968 --> 23:26.745
What is this?
Proof that some fain] tales are true.

23:27.406 --> 23:29.613
What am I looking at here?

23:29.708 --> 23:35.317
The real Santa Claus.
He tears naughty kids to pieces.

23:36.415 --> 23:38.588
Not even their skeletons are left.

23:38.651 --> 23:40.995
How did he end up there?

23:42.154 --> 23:48.435
[Sighs] The Sami people got angry
and lured him onto the ice.

23:48.494 --> 23:51.407
The ice broke under him.

23:51.463 --> 23:55.468
The lake froze solid
and Santa was trapped.

23:56.335 --> 24:01.785
Come summer,
they dug out the huge ice block...

24:01.840 --> 24:05.686
and buried it under
a sky-high pile of rocks.

24:07.346 --> 24:09.826
And it became Korvatunturi
Mountain? Yep.

24:12.318 --> 24:15.322
[ Laughs]
You're such an idiot.

24:16.255 --> 24:18.997
[Sighs]

24:19.658 --> 24:23.697
When did you last get smacked?
When I was little, I guess.

24:24.663 --> 24:26.643
Do you think we should confess?

24:32.004 --> 24:33.347
Listen, you brat.

24:33.439 --> 24:36.818
You have any idea
what your dad will do...

24:36.875 --> 24:40.823
when he hears that those
reindeer died because of you?

24:40.879 --> 24:44.053
[Engine Rumbling]

25:07.573 --> 25:11.419
Are you making gingerbreads?
Are you hungry?

25:13.879 --> 25:15.051
Yeah.

25:37.202 --> 25:39.910
[Sighs]

25:45.711 --> 25:47.554
Were you playing hockey?

25:47.613 --> 25:51.755
[Sighs]
No, it's just this game we play.

25:54.086 --> 25:56.225
Pretty rough game?

25:57.423 --> 25:58.424
Yeah.

26:03.595 --> 26:05.802
These are good.

26:06.899 --> 26:09.778
Just like Mum
used to make them.

26:10.536 --> 26:12.709
I'm glad to hear it.

26:15.574 --> 26:17.485
[Breathing Heavily]

26:25.951 --> 26:28.830
Dad, what if I didn't exist?

26:31.056 --> 26:33.434
What do you mean?

26:33.492 --> 26:35.631
If I disappeared.

26:38.564 --> 26:40.510
You should disappear...

26:41.166 --> 26:44.306
to your bed. It's late.

26:55.114 --> 26:59.256
Dad, do you think
I've been good?

27:01.587 --> 27:04.761
All good boys are in bed by now.

27:23.208 --> 27:25.313
Merry Christmas, Dad.

27:25.377 --> 27:27.687
Merry Christmas, Pietari.

27:42.127 --> 27:44.232
[SNIFFLES]

28:12.691 --> 28:18.039
[jingle Lightly]

28:23.368 --> 28:25.109
[Man On Radio In English]
This is Subzero One.

28:25.204 --> 28:28.083
[In English] Oh, finally.
We've tried contacting you a thousand times.

28:28.173 --> 28:28.878
Where are you?

28:28.941 --> 28:33.287
We are landing tomorrow
ls the cargo ready? No!

28:33.378 --> 28:35.051
We had to cancel
the whole operation.

28:35.113 --> 28:37.593
It's not what you think.
I repeat'

28:37.683 --> 28:40.061
<i>Is the cargo ready? <i></i></i>

28:40.118 --> 28:44.589
Cargo? Don't you understand?
It still has a pulse!

28:44.690 --> 28:49.400
<i>Calm down, Mr. Greene.
just follow the safety instructions.<i></i></i>

28:49.461 --> 28:51.304
Fuck your safety instructions!

28:51.396 --> 28:54.434
[Metallic Thumping]
What the fuck?

28:54.533 --> 28:56.069
[Men Veiling]

28:56.134 --> 28:58.444
[Wind Howling]

29:01.974 --> 29:04.580
DAYS TO CHRISTMAS

29:24.329 --> 29:25.933
[Chatter on Radio]

29:31.503 --> 29:35.007
[Wind Howling]

29:44.483 --> 29:46.861
[Yells]

29:56.094 --> 29:59.803
[In Finnish] Stay there.
I have to check it.

30:20.052 --> 30:23.795
Do you think this is funny?
I almost got killed.

30:26.892 --> 30:31.500
You are not going skating now!
You're grounded this Christmas.

30:31.563 --> 30:33.509
I have to wee.

30:39.071 --> 30:41.642
Come on, Vuppe. Let's go out.

30:54.486 --> 30:57.592
[Gasps]

31:06.431 --> 31:09.935
[Breathing Heavily]

31:10.669 --> 31:14.048
Dad! Dad!

31:17.042 --> 31:19.454
[ Rifle Cocks]

31:19.544 --> 31:22.684
What is it?
The bait's gone!

31:24.516 --> 31:26.723
[Zipper Zips]

31:35.894 --> 31:37.567
Careful now.

31:43.135 --> 31:44.978
Stay there.

31:49.641 --> 31:51.712
Did you hear me?

31:58.650 --> 32:00.891
Stay!

32:17.169 --> 32:18.773
Some kind of bird.

32:27.946 --> 32:29.448
What is it?

32:31.116 --> 32:32.424
Nothing.

32:33.084 --> 32:35.860
Can I look?
No.

32:36.688 --> 32:39.191
Some bird took the meat.

32:42.360 --> 32:45.773
I want to see it!
There's nothing down there.

32:46.264 --> 32:48.642
Why can't I look then?

32:48.700 --> 32:52.807
Because we haven't
even had breakfast yet.

33:02.814 --> 33:05.226
Is this really all we're having?

33:07.285 --> 33:08.559
These are good.

33:13.124 --> 33:17.231
If I eat these, can I go
and look down in the pit then?

33:18.396 --> 33:21.002
Then you'll have some more.

33:27.072 --> 33:29.211
Are you angry with me?

33:30.075 --> 33:31.247
NO.

33:32.577 --> 33:35.148
[Vehicle Approaches]

33:35.213 --> 33:36.715
Wait here.

33:37.582 --> 33:39.721
[Shouts]
Did you hear me?

33:41.586 --> 33:43.031
[Quietly]
You're grounded.

33:45.423 --> 33:49.235
[ Footsteps Leave]

33:49.327 --> 33:51.864
[Door Opens, Shuts]
[Father, In Finnish,Angrily]

33:51.930 --> 33:56.401
[ Man ] just preparing for my Santa gig.
[ Father] Shut up and follow me.

33:57.102 --> 33:59.378
[Whispers]
Come on, Vuppe.

34:24.295 --> 34:27.277
[Groans]
[ Exhales]

34:35.239 --> 34:38.312
He shouldn't have come snooping
around in people's yards.

35:04.836 --> 35:09.979
Greene, Brian Jonathan.

35:10.976 --> 35:13.456
Born 1952.

35:13.511 --> 35:16.151
Must be one of those nutters
from the mountain.

35:19.184 --> 35:21.357
Not even 60 years old.

35:25.190 --> 35:27.170
[Belll Jingles]

35:40.538 --> 35:43.144
[Sighs]

35:43.208 --> 35:45.347
What are you going to say?

35:46.778 --> 35:48.052
To who?

35:49.781 --> 35:51.124
Everyone.

35:55.453 --> 35:56.830
Nothing.

35:57.789 --> 36:00.633
You know those wolf pits are illegal.

36:00.692 --> 36:02.399
Darn it, Piiparinen!

36:04.229 --> 36:07.005
Like it or not, you're in this too.

36:07.065 --> 36:09.067
- I should-
- Shut up...

36:13.405 --> 36:16.249
and think, if you know how.

36:30.321 --> 36:33.768
I have an hour
to my first Santa stop.

36:54.512 --> 36:56.116
Vuppe, stay.

37:17.302 --> 37:20.408
[Machine Whirring]

37:29.214 --> 37:31.592
[Stops Machine]

37:31.649 --> 37:32.593
Did you see that?

37:43.294 --> 37:47.174
He's breathing.
Tough old codger.

37:57.675 --> 37:59.484
What is he doing?

38:00.311 --> 38:02.086
He smells something.

38:10.855 --> 38:12.027
Pietari.

38:16.027 --> 38:17.472
Pietari!

38:17.529 --> 38:19.531
You were supposed to
stay inside!

38:19.631 --> 38:22.373
Pietari,
come back here now!

38:23.535 --> 38:28.280
Did Pietari see him?
What do you think?

38:29.040 --> 38:32.681
I have to go,
What do I do with him?

38:32.777 --> 38:34.688
Have a little chat.

38:59.237 --> 39:00.875
The cops!

39:05.977 --> 39:07.718
Pietari, Pietari!

39:08.580 --> 39:11.083
Blast it all.

39:11.916 --> 39:14.089
[ Mutters]

39:27.065 --> 39:29.102
What's he up to?

39:53.691 --> 39:56.433
- Hiya.
- Hi.

39:56.527 --> 40:00.304
- Why the fancy dress?
- What?

40:00.932 --> 40:03.606
- Is everything in order?
- What do you mean?

40:04.702 --> 40:08.275
What a morning!
I've been all around the village.

40:08.940 --> 40:11.113
Strange stuff going on.

40:11.209 --> 40:16.488
Well, everything's fine here.
Right, Pietari?

40:17.482 --> 40:19.325
Then you're an exception.

40:23.621 --> 40:25.658
You brought
the whole murder squad?

40:25.757 --> 40:29.227
What's the problem here?
My other business.

40:29.827 --> 40:33.274
A couple of hundred sacks of
potatoes, my whole ha west.

40:33.331 --> 40:35.607
I'm here because of some potatoes?

40:35.667 --> 40:37.840
Yes and no.

40:41.172 --> 40:43.118
They only took the sacks.

40:46.678 --> 40:49.022
Holy mackerel.

40:49.113 --> 40:54.654
Almost every house got their
radiators stolen last night.

40:55.520 --> 40:57.864
Torn off the walls.

40:58.690 --> 41:01.330
It's going to be one cold Christmas.

41:02.860 --> 41:05.306
My wife's hair dryer was stolen
from the bathroom.

41:05.363 --> 41:08.037
Who'd want an old
piece of rubbish like that?

41:08.533 --> 41:13.380
It's cutting-edge technology
in Russia.

41:13.471 --> 41:16.350
- Pietari, we should be getting home.
- No!

41:17.675 --> 41:20.679
- Where's Juuso?
- Still sleeping, I guess.

41:25.183 --> 41:29.723
Not so fast.
Let's take a look at your car.

41:40.565 --> 41:42.476
Juuso.

41:54.345 --> 41:57.758
Juuso, wake up!
He's at our place now.

42:00.685 --> 42:01.891
Juuso!

42:13.398 --> 42:15.571
]Juuso's been taken!

42:17.268 --> 42:20.579
What the devil is that?
It was in Juuso's bed

42:20.671 --> 42:22.617
Maybe he's out chasing girls.

42:23.441 --> 42:26.251
When we were your age...

42:26.344 --> 42:29.416
we'd stack up some pillows
and pretend...

42:29.914 --> 42:31.552
He'll be back by nightfall.

42:31.616 --> 42:37.066
- Don't you get it?
- Pietari, that's enough!

42:38.790 --> 42:42.567
Can I go now?
Okay, go.

42:45.897 --> 42:48.969
Aimo, you speak English,
right?

42:50.635 --> 42:51.909
How come?

42:51.969 --> 42:54.609
We need an interpreter.

43:31.008 --> 43:33.147
Disgusting!

43:37.482 --> 43:38.483
[Whispers in English]
Hello?

43:40.952 --> 43:42.989
[In Finnish]
You old devil.

43:54.165 --> 43:55.667
[Sniffing]
Hmm?

44:00.204 --> 44:02.707
Gingerbread?

44:04.976 --> 44:06.182
Ah-ah.

44:13.851 --> 44:15.797
[ Bites]

44:16.654 --> 44:19.726
[Speaks Weakly]
Hmm?

44:19.824 --> 44:23.704
[Whispers]

44:33.704 --> 44:39.416
What do you want me to translate?
I've got stuff to do.

44:41.012 --> 44:43.356
We've got visitors
from Korvatunturi Mountain.

44:44.916 --> 44:49.729
Visitors?
American visitors.

44:56.060 --> 44:58.006
[Vehicle Approaches]

45:00.932 --> 45:02.878
[Engine Stops]

45:09.707 --> 45:11.880
Now, in you go.

45:11.943 --> 45:15.755
Daddy! We have to help Juuso.
Nonsense. Juuso is a big boy.

45:19.784 --> 45:21.730
So?

45:22.220 --> 45:25.064
We can't go back in there.
It's not human.

45:25.923 --> 45:27.800
Not human?
Not human!

45:27.892 --> 45:31.465
The old swine bit me!
Look at that.

45:33.064 --> 45:36.136
I have to see this.
I'm not kidding.

45:39.570 --> 45:41.481
[ Cocks Rifle]

45:48.913 --> 45:53.794
See for yourselves.
There's something really weird about him.

45:55.786 --> 45:58.665
- Don't you think?
- He's a foreigner.

46:00.825 --> 46:02.668
Go talk to him.

46:07.431 --> 46:09.638
Be careful.

46:10.668 --> 46:14.309
[In English] How do you like the
land of the northern lights?

46:25.316 --> 46:27.296
[Quietly, In Finnish]
I'm not going there alone.

46:28.452 --> 46:30.193
Right.

46:33.357 --> 46:35.337
Cover me.

46:41.198 --> 46:43.872
[ Rifle Cocks]

46:58.349 --> 47:00.556
He's harmless.

47:03.554 --> 47:05.727
[In English]
Wake up, Grandpa!

47:05.823 --> 47:07.496
[In English]
We need money.

47:08.225 --> 47:12.901
Sorry to disturb you on Christmas
Eve, but is Hemppa in?

47:15.166 --> 47:17.237
Oh, he isn't.

47:17.902 --> 47:19.745
Okay. Thanks anyway.

47:19.837 --> 47:21.817
No, I haven't seen him.

47:21.872 --> 47:24.352
Merry Christmas. Bye.

47:24.408 --> 47:27.150
[Phone Beeps]

47:34.585 --> 47:36.587
Give me the broom.

47:39.724 --> 47:43.194
[ Grunts ] [In English]
Where are your friends?

47:43.260 --> 47:46.104
[In Finnish] Ask him what
they were digging up.

47:47.565 --> 47:50.068
[In English] What did you
dig inside the mountain?

47:55.106 --> 47:57.950
[In Finnish]
He's acting deaf An old trick.

47:58.042 --> 48:02.422
Tell him we'll keep him here
until someone pays up.

48:05.249 --> 48:07.729
[Whispers] You mean as a hostage?
Yes.

48:09.453 --> 48:12.434
- Tell him!
- [ In English] We keep you here till somebody pay.

48:12.523 --> 48:15.561
[In Finnish] You're making him angry.
He doesn't understand you.

48:16.460 --> 48:18.804
[In Finnish]
This was just phase one.

48:21.465 --> 48:23.411
[ Rifle Cocks]

48:24.468 --> 48:26.880
[In English]
Last chance, asshole.

48:26.937 --> 48:30.578
Rauno here will
ask the next question.

48:30.641 --> 48:32.587
And he don't speak English.

48:32.643 --> 48:34.645
[ Knocking]
What was that?

48:34.745 --> 48:37.919
[ Pietari ] Dad!
[ Rauno] What does he want now?

48:37.982 --> 48:40.428
[ Pietari ]
Dad, I have to talk to you!

48:49.660 --> 48:55.838
I'm just doing a little job
with Piiparinen. What is it?

48:57.134 --> 48:59.011
You need to smack me.

49:00.504 --> 49:02.848
What?
I deserve to be smacked.

49:03.674 --> 49:07.315
Fifteen good lashes should do.

49:10.181 --> 49:12.161
What's the matter with you?

49:12.249 --> 49:14.661
[ Rattling]
I've been naughty.

49:14.752 --> 49:16.425
[ Banging]
[Men Shouting, Indistinct]

49:16.487 --> 49:17.693
What have you done?

49:17.788 --> 49:21.133
Juuso and I went up to the mountain,

49:21.192 --> 49:24.196
and we made that hole in the fence.

49:24.295 --> 49:25.467
You did what?

49:25.529 --> 49:28.032
I'm the only one left, Dad.

49:28.132 --> 49:30.976
All the others have been taken.
Juuso, too.

49:31.669 --> 49:33.478
What are you talking about?

49:33.537 --> 49:35.642
All the kids.

49:37.208 --> 49:39.552
Rauno, you have to see this.

49:39.643 --> 49:41.350
[Aimo Shouting]
Wait here.

49:51.522 --> 49:55.231
He's up to something.
And, look.

49:57.194 --> 49:59.196
He bit it in half.

50:10.241 --> 50:12.687
[ Rauno]
Look at his eyes.

50:16.580 --> 50:19.026
[Piiparinen]
What is he looking at?

50:22.419 --> 50:23.762
Pietari!

50:26.991 --> 50:28.095
Don't!

50:28.926 --> 50:31.532
Do you know this bloke
from somewhere?

50:33.931 --> 50:35.774
He seems to know you.

50:37.101 --> 50:39.103
He knows all the kids.

50:39.203 --> 50:41.444
Who is he?
Come on, speak up!

50:42.106 --> 50:44.279
He's been spying on us.

50:44.775 --> 50:47.449
What do you mean?
Tell me!

50:50.281 --> 50:52.921
He's Santa Claus.

51:04.061 --> 51:08.737
He's come to get me.
They dug him up from the mountain.

51:08.799 --> 51:10.904
A character from a fairy tale.

51:10.968 --> 51:14.745
I knew there was
something fishy going on.

51:15.639 --> 51:18.745
- He's going to attack!
- Daddy, don't let him take me!

51:18.809 --> 51:22.416
On the ground!
Tell him in English!

51:22.479 --> 51:24.755
[In English]
Down! Down boy!

51:24.815 --> 51:28.126
Go down!

51:28.218 --> 51:29.754
[In Finnish]
He has his own language.

51:30.321 --> 51:34.269
- [ Pietari] He's not afraid of you.
- He sure is.

51:34.325 --> 51:35.633
Tie him up.

51:35.726 --> 51:37.672
No way.
Now!

51:39.930 --> 51:42.137
[Squeaking]

51:50.107 --> 51:53.987
[Chains Squeaking]

52:08.792 --> 52:09.793
[Loud Static On Radio]

52:09.860 --> 52:12.363
What was that?

52:13.697 --> 52:17.543
[Man In English ] Subzero One.
Do you read me?

52:17.635 --> 52:19.637
[Aimo In Finnish]
It's coming from that jacket.

52:19.703 --> 52:21.842
Careful!

52:21.939 --> 52:25.386
<i>Mr. Greene?
ls everything okay? <i></i></i>

52:30.347 --> 52:32.156
[Man in English ]
We are landing in 30 minutes.

52:32.216 --> 52:35.789
What did he say?
They want him back.

52:39.490 --> 52:43.404
<i>[Man In English] Mr. Greene?
is Santa ready to fly? <i></i></i>

52:44.728 --> 52:46.730
Don't they?
What are you doing?

52:46.830 --> 52:48.741
Shh.

52:52.236 --> 52:53.874
[In Finnish]
This is Rauno.

52:54.905 --> 52:57.181
[In English]
Rauno from Finland.

53:12.923 --> 53:15.199
[In English]
We have Santa Claus.

53:15.259 --> 53:16.863
<i>[Man On Radio]
Who is this? <i></i></i>

53:16.927 --> 53:19.498
<i>[Man On Radio]
Where is Mr. Greene? <i></i></i>

53:19.563 --> 53:24.512
Tell him we have Santa
for sale.

53:50.761 --> 53:53.139
[ Cocks Gun ]

53:54.298 --> 53:56.710
How much are you
going to ask for him?

53:57.267 --> 53:59.747
Enough to cover the debt.
At least.

54:01.038 --> 54:03.541
Maybe we should think it over.
Are you scared?

54:05.142 --> 54:07.622
We're giving him up too easily.

54:07.711 --> 54:10.954
Just think what he could be worth.

54:12.249 --> 54:15.992
The original,
real Santa Claus.

54:17.254 --> 54:19.632
Someone is going to
get rich with him.

54:20.157 --> 54:21.932
That's the plan.

54:33.270 --> 54:35.181
[ Brakes Screech ]

54:36.673 --> 54:40.815
[ Helicopter Approaches]

54:40.911 --> 54:43.517
Dad!
Stay here, we won't be long.

55:09.373 --> 55:12.320
My wife's hair dryer!
What the hell...

55:12.376 --> 55:16.518
Put that hair dryer away.
Keep cool.

55:43.841 --> 55:45.650
What a midget.

56:00.858 --> 56:04.169
[In English] Who are you?
Where are my men?

56:08.198 --> 56:10.269
[In Finnish]
Say something.

56:10.367 --> 56:13.541
[In English] Yeah, yeah, We are men.
Let's do business.

56:13.604 --> 56:15.550
Business? What kind of business?

56:15.606 --> 56:18.382
What do you want?

56:19.743 --> 56:23.054
[In Finnish] How much do we want?
$85,000.

56:29.720 --> 56:31.290
[In English]
$85,000.

56:31.388 --> 56:34.961
[In Finnish] At least a million.
Shut up.

56:38.795 --> 56:42.299
[In English]
Hey. Where is the cargo?

57:26.343 --> 57:31.019
[Wind Howling]

57:49.700 --> 57:52.203
[In Finnish]
The last door.

58:25.402 --> 58:30.010
[In English] Shh!
Put down your weapons and smile...

58:31.475 --> 58:34.752
as nice as you can.

58:35.912 --> 58:41.590
And move slowly
and do exactly as I say.

58:42.185 --> 58:45.223
[In Finnish] What did he say?
We need to keep quiet,

58:46.189 --> 58:49.693
- [ In English] This is not Santa.
- What?

58:49.760 --> 58:53.105
It's one of Santa's little helpers.

58:54.364 --> 58:58.403
[In Finnish] What do you mean, a helper?
He says it's an el!!

58:58.935 --> 59:02.610
Enough of this rubbish!
Give us the money!

59:04.441 --> 59:05.613
[English Man]
God damn it.

59:06.443 --> 59:13.053
Santa is going to find out
who is naughty or nice.

59:13.116 --> 59:16.393
[Screaming]

59:20.057 --> 59:22.059
[In Finnish]
What's up with him?

59:23.527 --> 59:25.473
Is someone there?

59:28.231 --> 59:31.235
What's that running there?

59:36.073 --> 59:38.747
What on earth is happening here?

59:38.809 --> 59:41.312
[In English]
They're protecting their master.

59:42.479 --> 59:43.822
[Object Whirring]

59:46.616 --> 59:49.290
Pietari! Pietari!

59:59.596 --> 01:00:00.904
Pietari!

01:00:04.167 --> 01:00:06.613
[Rhythmic Thumping]

01:00:15.812 --> 01:00:18.019
The elves have built
a nest for Santa.

01:00:18.115 --> 01:00:21.096
[Heart Beating]

01:00:28.325 --> 01:00:29.463
For what?

01:00:29.526 --> 01:00:32.530
- Is that...
- Yes.

01:00:35.098 --> 01:00:37.510
They're trying to defrost him.

01:00:39.836 --> 01:00:42.646
[Quiet Whining]

01:00:44.975 --> 01:00:46.886
I Boy] Dad! Shh! What was that?

01:00:46.977 --> 01:00:49.514
I Boy]
Daddy, help.

01:00:50.013 --> 01:00:50.991
[Aimo]
Juuso.

01:00:51.047 --> 01:00:54.392
They're all here.
And soon they will get smacked.

01:00:57.154 --> 01:00:58.064
[Finnish]

01:00:58.889 --> 01:01:01.665
Dad!
Juuso, where are you?

01:01:02.893 --> 01:01:05.703
[Children Crying]
Turn off the heat!

01:01:05.795 --> 01:01:07.536
Juuso, say something.

01:01:09.332 --> 01:01:11.642
Piiparinen, the door won't hold!

01:01:12.402 --> 01:01:14.143
[Piiparinen]
What should I do?

01:01:14.204 --> 01:01:15.979
[Children Crying]
Barricade the door.

01:01:16.973 --> 01:01:19.852
Move these there!

01:01:19.910 --> 01:01:24.325
Aimo, leave the kid
and come and help us.

01:01:24.381 --> 01:01:25.223
Daddy's little boy.

01:01:27.184 --> 01:01:32.224
Let's go home, Daddy.
Don't worry, we'll get home soon.

01:01:34.257 --> 01:01:36.203
[Children Crying]

01:01:37.160 --> 01:01:39.265
We are all going to die!

01:01:56.780 --> 01:01:58.054
Dad!

01:02:00.050 --> 01:02:01.085
Aimo!

01:02:03.119 --> 01:02:04.792
Piiparinen!

01:02:04.888 --> 01:02:07.562
Listen to me!

01:02:22.372 --> 01:02:24.978
As long as the kids are here,

01:02:25.875 --> 01:02:28.822
the elves won't leave the hangar.

01:02:29.312 --> 01:02:31.588
It's either me or Santa.

01:02:36.286 --> 01:02:38.789
I suggest Santa.

01:03:47.991 --> 01:03:49.971
<i>It's Piiparinen. Pietari, do you read? <i></i></i>

01:03:50.460 --> 01:03:51.530
I do.

01:03:52.228 --> 01:03:54.572
<i>[Piiparinen In English] Ready
for takeoff.<i> Copy that.</i></i>

01:04:00.537 --> 01:04:02.847
Why do I have to go in the sack?

01:04:02.906 --> 01:04:05.853
Because it's my plan.
Let's go!

01:04:10.680 --> 01:04:13.752
Here's one more.
Not Juuso!!

01:04:14.351 --> 01:04:18.060
All the kids have to go,
or this won't work.

01:04:20.890 --> 01:04:26.101
Daddy, I'm scared.
Piiparinen, the package is ready.

01:04:30.367 --> 01:04:34.543
Won't they get cold out there?
Stay out of this.

01:04:36.773 --> 01:04:40.118
Don't worry, Dad. I'll be fine.

01:04:41.411 --> 01:04:43.789
Ready to go!

01:04:50.120 --> 01:04:53.932
You do your job, I'll deal with this!

01:05:40.136 --> 01:05:43.083
<i>[Pietari]
Slow down, we'll wait here.<i></i></i>

01:06:01.291 --> 01:06:03.794
Piiparinen, look down!

01:06:13.870 --> 01:06:19.047
<i>They're following us!<i>
What did I tell you?</i></i>

01:06:30.119 --> 01:06:33.123
Let's tum around, Piiparinen!

01:06:33.189 --> 01:06:34.566
What?

01:06:34.657 --> 01:06:38.833
- Towards the pens!
- What for?

01:06:38.895 --> 01:06:41.398
Pretend they are reindeer!

01:06:48.538 --> 01:06:51.576
Reindeer! Stars alive!

01:06:52.842 --> 01:06:54.685
That's what we'll do.

01:07:07.757 --> 01:07:11.933
Yahoo!

01:07:23.940 --> 01:07:25.749
[Sighs]

01:07:27.443 --> 01:07:29.047
Looks like we've been naughty.

01:07:36.419 --> 01:07:39.559
If you ever wondered
how Santa can be...

01:07:39.622 --> 01:07:44.435
in a zillion places all at once,
now you know.

01:07:46.462 --> 01:07:48.738
That's the magic of Christmas.

01:07:48.798 --> 01:07:52.211
[Chain Saw Revs]

01:07:53.903 --> 01:07:57.715
[Wind Blows]

01:08:04.113 --> 01:08:05.615
[Groans]

01:08:21.497 --> 01:08:24.171
Piiparinen, the gate's closed!

01:08:25.667 --> 01:08:29.810
<i>Fiddlesticks!
We need a new plan.<i></i></i>

01:08:29.906 --> 01:08:33.615
There isn't time!
I'll go and open it!

01:08:33.676 --> 01:08:35.986
<i>You're not going anywhere!<i></i></i>

01:08:36.078 --> 01:08:38.957
I can't land there
to bring you backup.

01:08:40.116 --> 01:08:42.095
I'm not coming back.

01:08:43.419 --> 01:08:45.524
Pietari can you hear me?

01:08:56.532 --> 01:08:58.136
Pietari!

01:09:42.310 --> 01:09:43.585
Piiparinen!

01:09:45.415 --> 01:09:48.487
Tell Dad what I did.

01:10:18.548 --> 01:10:20.050
Daddy

01:10:33.896 --> 01:10:35.569
Have a merry Christmas.

01:10:47.977 --> 01:10:50.924
And a happy bloody New Year.

01:11:13.836 --> 01:11:16.680
[Helicopter Whirs]
[ Laughter]

01:11:17.440 --> 01:11:21.115
How do you like that, elves?

01:11:21.177 --> 01:11:22.850
What happened?

01:11:22.945 --> 01:11:24.447
The miracle of Christmas.

01:11:24.514 --> 01:11:27.791
<i>Congratulations, Pietari! Congratulations!<i></i></i>

01:11:27.850 --> 01:11:30.330
You just put the elves out of a job.
[ Giggles I

01:11:45.201 --> 01:11:49.149
Take the kids home.
It's their bedtime.

01:11:50.206 --> 01:11:53.016
Roger. Over and out.

01:12:45.895 --> 01:12:48.375
198 Santa Clauses.

01:12:49.765 --> 01:12:52.109
Juuso, what's that worth?

01:12:57.573 --> 01:12:59.780
How much for one?

01:13:02.578 --> 01:13:04.114
$85,000.

01:13:14.423 --> 01:13:18.235
Around $16,800,000

01:13:18.928 --> 01:13:21.636
Plus 22% VAT.

01:13:39.749 --> 01:13:43.253
You're quite a man.
So are you.

01:13:58.834 --> 01:14:01.337
DAYS TO CHRISTMAS

01:14:18.354 --> 01:14:20.334
DAYS TO CHRISTMAS

01:14:42.211 --> 01:14:44.555
Nothing in there for you, fuzz face!

